revision.text:
{{Unreferenced|date=April 2007}}

A '''clean process oven''' is a type of [[Industry|industrial]] [[batch oven]] that is ideal for high-temperature applications, such as curing [[Polyimide]], and [[Annealing (metallurgy)|annealing]] thin and film waters. Clean process ovens may be for air atmospheres, or [[inert gas|inert atmospheres]] for [[oxidation]]-sensitive materials. Temperatures can be over 525 degrees Celsius. 

Other types of industrial batch ovens include [[laboratory]], [[Burn-in ovens|burn-in]], [[Reach-in oven|reach-in]], and walk-in/drive-in.

